<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>David Koblas writes:</p>

<p>Was doing some work with the base DB implementation and had the following suggestion...</p>

<p>Currrently (paraphrasing the doc example) to do an update you would have the following code.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$db-&gt;update(
    'round_table',
    array(
        'favorite_color' =&gt; 'yellow',
    ), 
    $db-&gt;quoteInto('first_name = ?', 'Robin')
);
</code></pre>

<p>It would be nice if update() could take a mixed third parameter so that you could write both the above statement (with lots of LIKEs and other
exprs) or it could take an array - yeilding:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$db-&gt;update(
    'round_table',
    array(
        'favorite_color' =&gt; 'yellow',
    ),
    array(
        'first_name' =&gt; 'Robin',
    )
);
</code></pre>

<p>Thus making it easier to do basic updates for keyed records, it would addtionally be handy to have it take an array for IN query sets.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$db-&gt;update(
    'round_table',
    array(
        'favorite_color' =&gt; 'yellow',
    ), 
    array(
        'first_name' =&gt; array('Robin', 'Joan', 'Julia'),
    )
);
</code></pre>

<p>--koblas</p>

<p>ps.  It would be nice to have it apply to delete()</p>

